  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3e1cd92da80c7495a8fe7eb91fa80c2f, type: 3}
  m_Name: Narcissus
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Plants.PlantData
  displayName: Narcissus
  audioClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 76a867b71ee24944e87fba3a06f1676c, type: 3}
  environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  poem:
    text: "Behold all the world's gardens and see \nthe traces of God's craft: \nwhere
      eyes of silver gaze on high, \nwith pupils made of molten gold, \non emerald
      stalks they testify \nthat God acknowledges no equal\n\n\u2014 Abu Nuwas"
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  contextInfos:
  - text: '## Narcissus

      Narcissus was the most beautiful. He rejected advances
      of all whom admired, so one asked him to be cursed. So he was, cursed to fall
      in love with him own reflection in a pool of water. He perished in agoning
      and longing, turning into the Daffodil.'
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  - text: "I wandered lonely as a Cloud \u2014 William Wordsworth\nI wandered lonely
      as a cloud\nThat floats on high o\u2019er vales and hills,\nWhen all at once
      I saw a crowd,\nA host, of golden daffodils;\nBeside the lake, beneath the
      trees,\nFluttering and dancing in the breeze.\n\nContinuous as the stars that
      shine\nAnd twinkle on the milky way,\nThey stretched in never-ending line\nAlong
      the margin of a bay:\nTen thousand saw I at a glance,\nTossing their heads
      in sprightly dance."
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
  - text: 'Mirza Ghalib:


      In order to see the greenery and the rose

      God
      has given the eye of the narcissus the power of seeing.'
    environmentPainting: {fileID: 0}
